  "title": "New Wave Your Behaviour",
  "description": "Veteran musician and performer Tor Lukasik-Foss uses a synthesizer, a drum machine, and some choice dance moves from the 1980’s to elevate his storytelling into something hilarious, heartfelt and unexpectedly urgent. ★★★★1/2 Winnipeg Free Press / ★★★★★Septimus Brown (Victoria Fringe) / CRITICS CHOICE Hamilton Fringe",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Tor Lukasik-Foss<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Mariló Núñez<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Tor Lukasik-Foss<br/>",
  "website": "https://torlukasikfoss.ca/project/new-wave-your-behaviour/",
  "plain_language": "What happens when a regular man suddenly loses his parent? Does he stop feeling like himself? Does he become unable to do his job anymore? Or does he get a keyboard and drum machine and focus on the pop music he loved as a kid? New Wave Your Behaviour is a funny, lively one-man show that uses pop songs to talk about grief, mental health, and how music stays in our heads.",
